Headline: Sources: for 2024, Apple is planning the iPad Pro's first major upgrade since 2018, featuring an M3, an OLED screen, and a Magic Keyboard with a larger trackpad
The US SEC charges Impact Theory, which sold NFTs, with offering unregistered securities, in a first; the LA-based entertainment firm agreed to pay a $6.1M fine
OpenAI launches GPT-4-powered Enterprise ChatGPT, with better privacy, performance, and data analysis features; pricing is “dependent on each company's usage”
DoorDash launches AI-powered voice ordering tech, giving restaurants a multi-language personalized voice ordering system with no missed calls or wait times
A look at the US Air Force's efforts to build an AI-based air combat system, including drones for as little as $3M apiece that serve pilots as a “loyal wingman”
A look at the ethical and legal issues around generative AI, which makes things that were previously only possible on a small scale practical at a massive scale
Chinese EV giant BYD's electronics unit plans to acquire US-based Jabil's manufacturing business in China for ~$2.2B; Jabil makes and assembles parts for Apple
The UK's NATS “identified and remedied” a network-wide computer failure earlier on August 28 that resulted in ~500 canceled flights and delayed hundreds more
Document: Lenovo plans to unveil on September 1 a €799 Legion Go gaming handheld, with an 8.8" 144Hz 2560×1600 display and 16GB RAM, and €499 Legion AR glasses
Filing: Didi plans to sell its smart car development arm to Xpeng, one of China's largest EV makers, for ~$744M in Xpeng stock, or a ~3.25% stake
Tesla faces its first trials over Autopilot allegedly causing crashes that killed the car's owner, in California court in September and Florida court in October
Sources: Intenseye, a workplace safety AI startup, is raising a $65M Series B led by Lightspeed at a ~$300M valuation, up from a ~$100M valuation in 2021
